                            <comment id="330129" author="hornc" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2022 16:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13896&quot; title=&quot;Reference leak in check for mr_forwarding&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13896&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13896&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="278086" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2020 23:30:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Serguei Smirnov (ssmirnov@whamcloud.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/39731&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/39731&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13923&quot; title=&quot;LNet: lnetctl &amp;quot;lnet unconfigure&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;net del&amp;quot; hangs if executed on a gateway&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13923&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13923&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: Add missing lnet_peer_ni_decref call&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 8564e47bc2d37102e742f8e688d87291ff39780a&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="278083" author="ssmirnov" created="Tue, 25 Aug 2020 22:06:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue has been introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13606&quot; title=&quot;Poor performance with routed clients to multi-rail servers when single server interface fails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13606&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13606&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38798&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38798&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The change added a call to lnet_nid2peerni_locked which is incrementing a reference on a peer_ni object which is never decremented. This results in LNet being unable to cleanup properly on &quot;unconfigure&quot; or &quot;net del&quot; operation, causing lnetctl to hang.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
